<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 06 at 8:15AM CST  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A wintry mix of snow, sleet, and freezing rain with minor
accumulations of ice...
Parts of central Arkansas will continue to see a mix of sleet,
freezing rain, and snow through the early morning hours Thursday.
Minor accumulations are possible with isolated slick areas,
especially on elevated surfaces. This may make travel difficult,
impacting morning commutes.</description>
